                        <h1>Developing a Developer</h1>
                        <p>A highly motivated IT professional with a wide area of technical knowledge, from Client/Enterprise solutions to web development. I work well under intense conditions, whether it be with a team or alone. I am go-getter and resourceful
                            person, yet I have no problems asking for help when necessary. I lead by example, and am responsible and dependable. I look forward to connecting with those of you who are looking to expand your professional network, as well
                            as those who could use my professional experience to their advantage.</p>
                        <p>I am a graduate from the University of North Texas, where I obtained a degree in Computer Science. I entered into the Information Technology professional world in 2005, where I landed the role of Assistant System Administrator
                            for a local law firm. Present day, I am a Technology Service Manager, where my primary focus is customer advocacy and helping customers optimize their IT solutions while reducing downtime and outages.</p>
                        <p>Recently I enrolled in a Bootcamp program, which begins in late-January of 2018 at Southern Methodist University. I am excited because I feel that it will be what I need to jumpstart my career as a full-stack developer. I have
                            a solid foundation with the front-end development - HTML, CSS and Javascript - but it is the back-end technologies that I have limited exposure. Once I have the confidence to approach and tackle back-end challenges, I will
                            feel more assure of my place in the development world.</p>
